# Adobe
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** software / digital media
**Website:** https://www.adobe.com

## Overview
Adobe Inc. is a multinational software company headquartered in San Jose, California, best known for its creative suite products including Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere Pro, and Acrobat Reader. Originally founded in 1982, Adobe pioneered desktop publishing and later expanded into digital marketing, document management, and cloud-based creative tools through its Creative Cloud subscription model. The company’s tools are widely used by designers, photographers, videographers, and marketing professionals worldwide, making it a cornerstone of the digital content creation ecosystem.

## Utah connection
Adobe has a major presence in Utah’s Silicon Slopes region, with a large office in Lehi that houses engineering, product development, and customer support teams. The Utah location is one of Adobe’s key engineering hubs outside of its California headquarters, contributing significantly to the state’s tech employment base and helping solidify Utah’s reputation as a center for software innovation. Adobe has also partnered with local universities and tech organizations, further integrating itself into the state’s growing technology community.

